 was elected prime minister of Japan|prime minister by the National Diet on 1 October.]]
{{Shigeru Ishiba sidebar}}
On 30 September 2024, former Minister of Defense (Japan)|Minister of Defense Shigeru Ishiba, who won the heated nine-way contest in the 2024 Liberal Democratic Party (Japan) presidential election|party presidential election on 27 September, officially announced that he would call an early election to be held on 27 October, a year ahead of the expiration of the current term, to seek confidence from the people. After his inauguration as the prime minister on 1 October, the House of Representatives (Japan)|House of Representatives was dissolved on 9 October, with the election being announced on the 15th, and voting to take place on the 27th.

